{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὅμηρος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>pledge, surety, hostage,</b> ὁμήρους λαμβάνειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.99; ὁ. παῖδας λαβών [prev. author] 1.64; τὰ ἑωυτοῦ τέκνα δοὺς ὁ. [prev. author] 7.165, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.83; ἐν ὁμήρων λόγῳ ποιεύμενος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.222 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄγεσθαι ὅμηροι to be carried off <b>as hostages,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 8.94, 9.90 \">Refs</a>]; τοῖον ὅμηρόν μ᾽ ἀποσυλήσας having robbed me of such <b>a hostage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 870 (_anapaest meter_) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἔχω γ᾽ ὑμῶν ὁμήρους have <b>hostages</b> for you, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 327, compare “Lys.” 244 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of things, τὴν γῆν ὅμηρον ἔχειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.82: _neuter_ _plural_, ὅμηρα δούς 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 12.68, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.52.5, “OGI” 751.5 (2nd c.BC) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὥσπερ.. ὁμήρους ἔχομεν τοῦ λόγου τὰ παραδείγματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 202e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>neuter</i> <i>plural</i> even of one person, μὴ πεμψάτω ὅμηρα τῶν Αἰαντείων μηθένα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Schwyzer” 366.17 (from Tolophon) \">Refs</a>]; ὃς ἦν ὅμηρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Mac.1.10. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G8505","accentedUnicode":"ὅμηρος","shortDef":"a security treaty","mediumDef":"a security treaty","stepGloss":"a security treaty","stepTransliteration":"homēros","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}